Thousands of Postgraduate Certificate in Education students are financially stranded. Courtesy #DStv403 CAPE TOWN - Thousands of Postgraduate Certificate in Education students are financially stranded. The National Student Financial Aid Scheme states on its website, that as of 2021, it will no longer provide funding for postgraduate courses but for some students, finding out that they too won't get support, has come as a complete shock. WATCH: Student protests set to continue eNCA's Monique Mortlock shares more details in the video above. Editor's Note: NSFAS is yet to react eNCA inquiries. We will give you that response when we get it.